line_1: Thro' greyish mists behold Aurora dawns,
line_2: Crouching to earth his guileful pointer fawns,

line_1: 'When the sky opens and the evening dawns!
line_2: 'Oh sweet as dew-drops on these flowery lawns,

line_1: Not half so sweet, when first the Morning dawns,
line_2: Are juicy Oysters, or the luscious Prawns.
